# Match Cut — engraved practices

Read `docs/GOOD_PRACTICES.md` and `AGENTS.md` before non-trivial edits.

## MUST

- Keep all image processing client-side (MediaPipe, canvas, FFmpeg.wasm). Never upload user photos to a server or external vision API without explicit approval.
- Preserve export basename `` `match-cut-${Date.now()}` `` for GIF/MP4 downloads.
- Put pipeline logic in `lib/`; keep React components thin. Do not add features to `app/page.tsx` — extract `hooks/` first.
- Fix GIF and MP4 export paths independently; smoke-test Chrome after changes to `videoExport.ts`, `imageAlignment.ts`, or `faceDetection.ts`.
- Surgical diffs only. Match TypeScript + Tailwind style. Use `@/` imports.
- Document user-visible changes in README; architecture changes in `docs/STRUCTURE.md`.
- New dev notes go in `docs/history/` or `docs/decisions/` — never `*_FIX.md` at repo root.
- Pass `npm run lint`, `npm run build`, and `npm run check:practices` before considering work done.

## MUST NOT

- Add server-side image storage or third-party face APIs without approval.
- Grow `app/page.tsx`, `lib/beatDetection.ts`, or `lib/videoExport.ts` with new concerns — split modules instead.
- Break `next.config.js` wasm/COOP settings without testing export.
- Force-push `main` on `extendedvoidvoid/match-cut`.

